<br>
When mob dies, go through the damage dealt list. For each person on that list who is alive and in the zone, credit their damage to their group. Now, determine which group did the most damage, give the exp to them. If that group is part of a raid, then the experience is divided up among the raid.<br>
<br>
So in this case, the wizard did more damage than any other individual group. If one of those groups included two damage dealers of any other kind (e.g. a magician and a monk), this shows that wizards need a nice tall glass of STFU.<br>
<br>
If none of the other groups had two living damage dealers when Tallon died, then it just illustrates the biggest problem with money grubbing Verant's idiotic implementation of raid experience. Raids were supposed to make ninja looting no longer a problem, but it doesn't solve that because they didn't implement it well. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
