<br>
It gets easier to be awarded credit for a kill as the number of groups increase. Once you start getting more and more groups in on a kill, each group is contributing less overall damage since your raid's total DPS goes up while the mobs hitpoints remain constant. So each group is doing a lesser share of the mobs hitpoints. So a high DPS class like wizard can individually do more damage than any one of the other groups and be awarded the kill. It's pretty situational, but I've seen it happen and even managed to take advantage of it myself on occasion.<br>
<br>
You've probably even seen this on raids that later add more groups. Maybe it seemed early on it was tougher to nab xp than later on when there were more groups present and getting xp required fewer nukes.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
Taeru<br>
